    "description": "A modern village near the coast north from Chennai where an archaeologically attested seaport settlement flourished from the 3rd century BCE until the 15th century CE as attested by remnants of Chinese and Thai pottery -- as well as a Chinese coin. It is probably to be identified with Ptolemy's \"Kottis\".",
    "details": "<p>The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: Kottapattinam?</p>",
